programme.desc: Was Mary Magdalene murdered? Did the Catholic Church conspire to eradicate the Holy Bloodline from existence? To some Mary Magdalene was the wife or consort of Jesus Christ. The arena along with the idea of a Holy Bloodline descended from Jesus and Mary. In this unique film we journey to places never before researched in connection with this story. programme.title: Paranormal Horrors of The True North
programme.desc: Canada has a rich and colorful history which has resulted in a variety of paranormal phenomena from coast to coast. Outdoor enthusiasts hiking the Bruce Trail in Ancaster, Ontario often find themselves at the remains of a once great mansion. Known as the Hermitage Ruins, visitors encounter two very different spirits on a regular basis. The first is a coachman who hung himself on the property and still carries the severed noose around his neck. The second apparition is a woman who once owned the mansion and loved it so much that she refused to leave even after it burned down. The “Espirit” is Montreal’s hottest nightclub. While it has had many names over the years, one thing has remained constant – it’s ghostly apparitions. During the latest renovations, many workers witnessed a large ball of light floating towards them, and even passing through them. Others saw the ghost of a woman, with a horrific scar running the length of her pale torso. The War of 1812 was a definitive moment in Canadian history, inflicting thousands of casualties. One fight in particular left an impression on Niagara Falls, Ontario. The Battle for Lundy’s Lane was so grueling; it claimed hundreds of lives in mere hours. Welcome to Our Wyld Life where host Kristy Titus and her husband, Yogi, take viewers along on their day-to-day lives, full of adventure. After relocating to Wyoming, hunting, outdoor and shooting sports recreation are literally in their backyard. The couple is truly making their home on the range while developing their new homestead and enjoying life in the cowboy state.

After a tough start, Kristy makes it a great week with familiar faces and many new ones, in what is one of the most fun shows of the year! If you didn't make it in 2023, it's a must to attend next year! Also, you'll be introduced to the newest (and longest eared) members of the family! Kristy shows off her baby mules...lots more of the mules to come! The Farm on Central is proving what can be accomplished with dedication to the future of farming.

programme.title: Farm Hero
programme.desc: On this episode, Laura takes a trip to White Oak Pastures in Georgia to meet with pioneer and visionary, Will Harris. After two decades of monocultural farming, Will took his multi-generation farm into a completely new direction by turning it into a regenerative farm. Through trials and tribulations, Will and his family are paving the way for regenerative agriculture and educating the public on the importance of food education.

programme.title: Tiny Paradise
programme.desc: A free spirit has found her desert paradise and is working to fulfill her dream of building a tiny home eco-village on 10 acres in Joshua Tree, CA. This artistic endeavor will be quite the undertaking as they battle the desert elements and a tight timeline. The unique, transforming tiny will have two halves connected by an atrium and will feature multiple Murphy beds, handmade countertops, a mural and a rock garden.

programme.title: Tiny Paradise
programme.desc: A family plans to build a low-impact hobbit house that capitalizes on breathtaking views and overlooks their barn in the mountains of North Carolina. The partially underground tiny house will have a rock fire pit and cedar hot tub outside, and a modern Euro-feel inside with plenty of built-in storage and floor-to-ceiling windows.

programme.title: Tiny Paradise
programme.desc: An architect takes his plans for a unique tiny house to the middle of the Arizona desert. The build will have legs so it won't disrupt the desert landscape as well as plenty of interesting angles and different uses of metals. This home will take open-concept to the next level with translucent window walls and a completely open kitchen and bathroom that allows the warm desert air to move through the house. Industrial elements are used throughout the build from toolboxes for kitchen cabinets and an airplane wing as part of the roof framing to Japanese-style room separators and an experimental hatch skylight.

programme.title: Tiny Paradise
programme.desc: A family has found a slice of paradise on a small island in the Bahamas and is ready to start building their dream home. Although this beautiful location comes with a harsh landscape and threat of hurricanes, the family is determined to have a tiny cliffside shack overlooking the ocean. The beautifully handcrafted house is sided in thatch and blends in perfectly with its surroundings. With its surfboard storage, deck flooring, outdoor shower and jaw-dropping views, this family's dream home is the ultimate place to relax.

programme.title: Tiny Paradise

programme.title: Preview For Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks

The crisp, snowy high‑Sierra peaks in the distance add a stunning alpine contrast that evokes calm and wonder. Altogether, the film crafts a tranquil escape into natures beauty—perfect for relaxation, reflection, or simply drifting off into nature’s embrace. The full 90 minute film is available to subscribers of NatureStream.tv.

programme.desc: Ernie Lijoi is an agent for the Quincy, MA police department, working in tandem with FBI and DEA. An informant tips him off that a crew of bank robbers are looking to sell $800,000 in stolen bonds. Lijoi goes undercover and pretends to want to buy the bonds, while he builds a case against the robbers. He meets the bank robbers in a courtroom to broker the deal and sets a trap to take everyone involved down - including the informant.

programme.title: Operation Whiskey 12: Undercover Attack
programme.desc: Nate Hutchinson is part of an undercover team in Ogden, UT while working for the Weber County Sheriff's Department. After years of undercover operations involving small time drug dealing, the team pays a call to an illegal pot grower. A seemingly routine call explodes when the grower ambushes and shoots five undercover agents, killing one. Hutchinson exhibits unbelievable acts of bravery to save his fellow officers, and miraculously survives being shot 5 times. He returns to the force and the undercover team, driven to have the last word on the cowardly attacker.

programme.title: Operation Whiskey 12: Undercover Attack
programme.desc: Nate Hutchinson is part of an undercover team in Ogden, UT while working for the Weber County Sheriff's Department. After years of undercover operations involving small time drug dealing, the team pays a call to an illegal pot grower. A seemingly routine call explodes when the grower ambushes and shoots five undercover agents, killing one. Hutchinson exhibits unbelievable acts of bravery to save his fellow officers, and miraculously survives being shot 5 times. He returns to the force and the undercover team, driven to have the last word on the cowardly attacker.

programme.desc: Ernie Lijoi is an agent for the Quincy, MA police department, working in tandem with FBI and DEA. Lijoi goes undercover and pretends to want to buy the bonds, while he builds a case against the robbers. He meets the bank robbers in a courtroom to broker the deal and sets a trap to take everyone involved down - including the informant.

programme.title: Ashes To Ashes
programme.desc: At Lake Mohave, Nevada, a fisherman stumbles across a human skull. In the North West of England, a husband claims his wife has left him for another man. But where is she?

programme.title: Operation Stolen Bonds: Duping Wise Guy Robbers
programme.desc: Ernie Lijoi is an agent for the Quincy, MA police department, working in tandem with FBI and DEA. An informant tips him off that a crew of bank robbers are looking to sell $800,000 in stolen bonds. Lijoi goes undercover and pretends to want to buy the bonds, while he builds a case against the robbers. He meets the bank robbers in a courtroom to broker the deal and sets a trap to take everyone involved down - including the informant.

programme.title: Operation Whiskey 12: Undercover Attack
programme.desc: Nate Hutchinson is part of an undercover team in Ogden, UT while working for the Weber County Sheriff's Department. After years of undercover operations involving small time drug dealing, the team pays a call to an illegal pot grower. A seemingly routine call explodes when the grower ambushes and shoots five undercover agents, killing one. Hutchinson exhibits unbelievable acts of bravery to save his fellow officers, and miraculously survives being shot 5 times. He returns to the force and the undercover team, driven to have the last word on the cowardly attacker.

programme.title: Operation Stolen Bonds: Duping Wise Guy Robbers
programme.desc: Ernie Lijoi is an agent for the Quincy, MA police department, working in tandem with FBI and DEA. An informant tips him off that a crew of bank robbers are looking to sell $800,000 in stolen bonds. Lijoi goes undercover and pretends to want to buy the bonds, while he builds a case against the robbers. He meets the bank robbers in a courtroom to broker the deal and sets a trap to take everyone involved down - including the informant.

programme.title: Operation Whiskey 12: Undercover Attack
programme.desc: Nate Hutchinson is part of an undercover team in Ogden, UT while working for the Weber County Sheriff's Department. After years of undercover operations involving small time drug dealing, the team pays a call to an illegal pot grower. A seemingly routine call explodes when the grower ambushes and shoots five undercover agents, killing one. Hutchinson exhibits unbelievable acts of bravery to save his fellow officers, and miraculously survives being shot 5 times. He returns to the force and the undercover team, driven to have the last word on the cowardly attacker.
